  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM Appeal Rohingya Humanitarian Crisis 2019</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims at ensuring comprehensive humanitarian and COVID-19 assistance through the provision of water, sanitation and hygiene services for Rohingya refugees are maintained and monitored to prevent disease outbreaks, uphold the dignity of the population and strengthen relationships between refugees and the host community. In addition, IOM is providing protection services to prevent and respond to gender-based violence, child abuse, human trafficking and other protection risks, incidents and threats in the camp settlements and host communities. Where IOM directly manages camps, site management continues to strengthen the coordination of stakeholders working at camp-level as well as service monitoring to ensure that there are no duplication or gaps in service provision.</narrative>
  </description>
